Definition: a currency that is not likely to depreciate suddenly in value
Example: the countries agreed to conduct their bilateral trade in hard currency, replacing previous barter arrangements; Germany once had a solid economy, good fiscal and monetary policies, and a hard currency
Synonyms: currency, a, that, is, not, likely, to, depreciate, suddenly, in, value, the, countries, agreed, conduct, their, bilateral, trade, hard, replacing, previous, barter, arrangements, Germany, once, had, solid, economy, good, fiscal, and, monetary, policies
Category: noun.possession
